---
/**
 * SocialIcons — X (Twitter)/Instagram icon pair for Footer's `social-icons`
 * slot.
 *
 * Ported from the real rendered reference (`cinematen-data.js` socialEls`) —
 * plain outline-style glyphs (`color: var(--on-surface-variant)`, no filled
 * background pill), not the old BaseFooter.astro filled-circle Facebook +
 * Instagram icons. New primitive — not part of the _ds_bundle export, which
 * didn't ship a social-icons component at all.
 */
---

{/* No confirmed real X/Twitter account exists anywhere in this codebase
    (legacy BaseFooter.astro only ever had Facebook + Instagram) — the
    reference mock itself links this icon to href="#" rather than a real
    profile, so this isn't a placeholder invented here; it's matching the
    source exactly rather than fabricating an unconfirmed account URL. */}
<a
  href="#"
  class="cn-social-link"
  aria-label="Cinematen op X"
>
  <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path
      d="M18.244 2H21.5l-7.5 8.57L23 22h-6.8l-5.32-6.96L4.8 22H1.54l8.02-9.17L1 2h6.96l4.8 6.36L18.244 2Zm-1.19 18h1.83L7.03 3.9H5.06L17.054 20Z"
    ></path>
  </svg>
</a>
<a
  href="https://www.instagram.com/cinematen_podcast"
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener"
  class="cn-social-link"
  aria-label="Cinematen op Instagram"
>
  <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
